=
Express the unit vectors $vu(r), vu(theta), vu(phi)$ in terms of $vu(x),vu(y),vu(z)$. Check your answers several ways\
($vu(r) dot vu(r) eq.quest 1, vu(theta) dot vu(phi) eq.quest 0, vu(r) times vu(theta) eq.quest vu(phi), dots $). Also work out the inverse formulas, giving $vu(x), vu(y), vu(z)$ in terms of $vu(r), vu(theta), vu(phi)$ (and $phi, theta$).

/*
#solution[

*$r$-component*:

The $vb(r)$-vector is simply 
$
  vb(r) = x vu(x) + y vu(y) + z vu(z)
$
and its unit vector is
$
  vu(r) = vb(r)/r = (x vu(x) + y vu(y) + z vu(z))/sqrt(x^2 + y^2 + z^2)
$

